    Scope and Contents
Records of the Office of Continuing Education include chronological listings of events at SSU, administrative statistics and program recommendations.  Events include: lectures by Mark Heyman, Margaret Sloan, Ray Marchall, Tom Hamlstead, Cullom Davis, Charles Schweighauser and Gene Roddenberry.  Topics include: "White Man looks at the Back man's World; Community Energy Self-Reliance; Patterns of Interaction in the Family;  the New U.S. China  Policy; and Law Enforcement &amp; the Elderly."  Administrative statistics provide information regarding how many graduate and undergraduate students attended each event. Program recommendations are from participating faculty and staff and provides suggestions for new topics to be offered and how to improve existing lectures an presentations.  
  
